Written evidence submitted by Resolution (LAI 004)[bold]Transforming Legal Aid[bold]This evidence sets out some of the issues raised by the proposed 
[normal]introduction of a residence test for legal aid claimants in children and family cases.
[normal]About Resolution [bold]Resolution, which was formerly known as the Solicitors Family Law Association (SFLA), is an organisation of 6,500 members who believe in a constructive
[normal], non‐confrontational approach to family law matters. Resolution also campaigns for improvements to the family justice system. 
[normal]For further information [bold]please contact Rachel Rogers, Resolution’s Head of Policy: 
[normal]rachel.rogers@resolution.org.uk 
[normal]/ 020 3195 01
[normal]89, or Matt Bryant, Director of Communications: 
[normal]matt.bryant@resolution.org.uk 
[normal]/ 020 3195 0190.
